BLUETONGUE, LIVESTOCK - BRAZIL: OIE REPORT
******************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 10 Oct 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/alerte/en_bra091001.HTM>

Translation of an e-mail received on 9 Oct 2001 from Dr Paulo Lourenco da
Silva, Director, Department of Animal Protection, Ministry of Agriculture
and Food Supply, Brasilia:
Report date: 8 Aug 2001.
One outbreak of bluetongue has been reported in Campo Tenente, Parana State.
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 24 May 2001.
Estimated date of first infection: 23 Apr 2001.
Total number of animals in the outbreak:
species / susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
ovi / 130 / 8 / 3 / 127 / 0
cap / 4 / 1 / 1 / 3 / 0
bov / 70 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 0
Diagnosis:
Laboratory where diagnosis was made: Pan American Foot-and-Mouth Disease
Center (Rio de Janeiro).
Diagnostic tests used: polymerase chain reaction.
Control measures:
- stamping out;
- the affected property has been placed under quarantine.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
.....................mhj/pc/pg/es
